                            <comment id="16013715" author="btellier" created="Wed, 17 May 2017 08:20:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem was larger: any mail sent by a mailet was not relayed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As this is a bit of a problem, we propose, by default:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To add an attribute when the email is sent by a mailet&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Allow finer grained relay management, per protocol (SMTP, JMAP, and automatically sent). We added specific matcher to detect, based on attributes, if a mail is sent by JMAP. Thus relaying is abstracted with another attribute: RelayAllowed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;No regression was introduced in these configuration changes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/linagora/james-project/pull/777&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/linagora/james-project/pull/777&lt;/a&gt; is solving this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
